text: Restoran yang sangat luas, asri, nyaman, dengan masakan jamur yang sangat bervariasi dan enak-enak. Rekomen sate jamur, sambal jamur pedas. Jangan lupa cobain gelato jamur yang rasanya unik. Gak ketinggalan juga bermacam oleh-oleh berbahan dasar jamur. Terapi kaki dengan ikan merupakan pengalaman seru di sini.

title: Jejamuran
name: Dhian S.
text: Parkiran luas, berada di seberang Restoran. Kamar mandi bersih dan wangi meski terlihat agak usang namun tetap terawat. Varian masakan aneka jamur dan pelengkapnya banyak, enak, dan terjangkau. Ada terapi ikan gratis, sangat berguna bagi pengunjung yang lelah perjalanan. Terdapat wisata edukasi lokasi terpisah dari Restoran. Sangat cocok sebagai destinasi wisata healing bersama keluarga.

title: Jejamuran
name: Thu Huddleston
text: Restoran yang awalnya hanya kecil sekarang berkembang menjadi besar. Setahu saya ini adalah pionir olahan dari bahan jamur yang aman untuk dikonsumsi. selain menikmati makanannya yang sangat lezat, pengunjung dapat melihat pengembangbiakan jamur. recommmended

title: Jejamuran
name: SEPTIANA DEWI NURINDAH PRISTA
text: Udah kedua kalinya kesini, rasanya sama ga berubah enakk mantep, syahdu juga pas hujan kesininya

title: Jejamuran
name: John The Explorer
text:
Recommended banget klo ke Jogja dan harus makan disini. Tapi terus terang Satenya dulu lebih enak dr pd skrg2 ini. Dulu waktu makan satenya agak berasa makan sate ayam pd hal terbuat dr jamur. Klo skrg makan satenya ya cm berasa bener2 sate jamur. Berasa kyk ayamnya sdh gk ada lagi. Entah kenapa agak beda dengan dulu2. Mungkin kokinya gantikah?

Tapi menu paling wajib dan juara seh tetep Tongsengnya ya. Layak diorder pertama kali d. Hampir semua menunya enak2 seh. Jd mau order menu apapun gk usah mikir2 lg d.

Sekarang restonya makin besar. Dulu sebelah kirinya yg parkiran mobil dan diperbaruin dan menjadi restoran jg. Ada kolam ikannya dan skrg ada mini martnya khusus jual snack jamur2an yg sdh digoreng kering. Enak2 seh dan ada tasternya setiap rasa. Trus sample gardening jejamurannya dipindahkan ke depan restoran sebelum gerbang utama. Jd disana pengunjung bisa melihat dan memegang secara detail bagaimana cara berbudidaya jejemuran. Bagus buat pengetahuan anak2.

title: Jejamuran
name: Erdin 888
text: Menunya unik ala jamur, tempatnya enak untuk makan bareng keluarga, ada kolam ikan, kebun kelinci, dan terapi ikan. Harga kategori terjangkau

title: Jejamuran
name: Audi Julianto
text: Overall utk rasa makanan nya enak, apalagi ada menu paket keluarga yg cukup terjangkau. Utk suasana nya oke menarik dan ada market yg menjual produk oleh²

title: Jejamuran
name: Kotekaz
text:
Berlokasi di Pendowoharjo, Sleman. Sebagian besar menu yang tersedia disini merupakan olahan dari jamur tiram, jamur kuping, jamur portabello dan beberapa jenis jamur lainnya. Ada olahan sate jamur, fuyunghai jamur, jamur tepung, martabak jamur dll. Cukup lezat untuk menunolahan jamur.
Harga termasuk standard untuk rumah makan, tidak murah, tidak terlalu mahal juga. Dengan suasana yang asri, menemani waktu untuk menikmati makanan.

title: Jejamuran
name: Farid Elfarisy
text:
Mantab Bener...!!!
Menu yang disajikan sangat beragam, banyak aneka menu dengan berbahan dasar jamur yg rasanya nendang di lidah. Untuk para petualang kuliner, sangat recomended utk memuaskan selera. Klo saya menu favoritnya tongseng jamur. Tempat sangat luas, jangan khawatir ga kebagian tempat. Toilet lumayan bersih, penyajian menu jg ga terlalu lama. Parkiran gede, muat banyak mobil dan bus. Anak2 pada seneng, ada terapi ikan gratis, dan ada display baglog beberapa jenis jamur. Super pokoknya, ga rugi kesini...

title: Jejamuran
name: Samwanwan
text:
Pelayanan bagus. Masuk langsung dilayani dan diarahkan ke meja. Setelah pesan menu waktu tunggu untuk makanan datang relatif cepat.

Tempatnya bersih dengan atmosfir yang hijau penuh tanaman, sangat menenangkan. Tempat hygienis dengan tempat cuci tangan bersih & sabun selalu terisi, meja makan bersih & ada tisu selalu terisi, penyajian sendok 1 set terbungkus plastik. Toilet dan mushola ada tapi tidak sempat mampir. Arah keluar setelah makan terdapat kolam terapi ikan, jual tanaman hias, merchendise dan oleh-oleh khas jamur.

Menu utama banyak sekali varian menu jamur, saya sebagai pecinta daging agak pesimis bakal kenyang nggak ya, karena biasa jamur hanya sebagai side dish. Ternyata sangat bisa jadi main dish dan porsi normal dengan 1 main dish sudah cukup mengenyangkan. Untuk yang tidak suka jamur ada alternatif menu ikan dan ayam. Bila tidak habis makanan bisa dibungkus untuk take away.

title: Jejamuran
name: Ira Luvyra
text: Masakan enak, pelayanan cepat, tempat parkir sangat luas, harga sesuai rasa, manajemen restonya bagus, sayangnya waktu kesana musik jawanya sudah selesai, mungkin musik jawanya lebih bagus jika sampai restorannya tutup. Buku menu mungkin ada yang butuh untuk diganti karena ada banyak coretan dan berbau. Ada berbagai produk makanan dari jamur untuk oleh-oleh. (1 Feb 2020 20:30)

title: Jejamuran
name: Indra Riansyah
text:
Hampir semua menunya menggunakan bahan dari berbagai jenis jamur. Namun rasanya seperti tidak makan jamur. Sate jamur tapi rasanya seperti makan sate kambing atau sate ayam. Enak sekali.

Jam 12.00 siang suasana sangat ramai namun masih banyak tempat kosong. Menunggu makanan juga tidak lama. Untuk pengunjung sebanyak itu hanya menunggu tidak sampai 30 menit semua pesanan sudah disajikan.

Tempat makan luas, parkiran juga luas. Di dalam ada musholla.

title: Jejamuran
name: Neiska Syahraneissa
text:
Lahan parkir luas, gratis parkir juga. Bahkan di tempat parkir di sediakan kamar mandi dan mushola.

Di restonya sendiri cukup luas, dan dekoratif. Banyak tanaman yang menyejukkan mata. Ada stand merchandise juga. Ada terapi ikan pula👌

Pelayanan sangat baik, resto ramah lansia dan kaum disabilitas. Menu serb jamur dan lezat💕💕

title: Jejamuran
name: Hilwah Rahmawati
text: Tempat strategis di pinggir jalan, tempat nya asri adem banyak dedaunan dan pepohonan, makanan enak pelayanan cepat ramah, berbagai menu utama olahan jamur, tp untuk makannya td pas makan siang ada beberapa yg dingin kurang hangat/fresh, harga nya terjangkau, dan tempat selalu ramai pengunjung

title: Jejamuran
name: Astika E
text: Udah lama banget gak kesini tapi rasanya masih sama. Bener-bener authentic, rasanya bner-bener Indonesia banget kalau menurut saya. Kalau seukuran jamur ya emang mahal sih menurut saya, 15ribuan keatas semua, tapi rasanya sumpah worth it banget! Sekarang tempatnya diperbesar jadi luas banget, jadi mereka menyediakan kereta-keretaan buat para pengunjung yang memakirkan kendaraanya di tempat yang jauh. Jamur yang diolah bermacam-macam banget, dari jamur rada ekslusif sampai jamur yang familiar banget, seperti tiram, merang, dll. Yang favorit menurut saya sih satenya ya. So chewy, kayak makan daging ayam yang super kenyel-kenyel gitu. Mereka menyediakan semacam bibit-bibit jamur yang bisa dibeli. Juga berbagai macam olahan jamur untuk oleh-oleh.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nurul Izzah Aisyah
text:
Sate jamur shitakenya enak. Begitu masuk disambut dengan jamur2 yang masih hidup. Di deket tempat makannya ada gratis terapi ikan.
Menu rekomendasi sate jamur, dadar jamur, rendang jamur

title: Jejamuran
name: Satria Gradienta
text: makanannya enak, banyak menu dari jamur, tempatnya juga nyaman dan bersih, lokasinya sejuk, banyak tempat buat makanya, lokasi tempat terlihat dari jalan ramai lancar

title: Jejamuran
name: ineke amandha
text:
Tempat ini punya first impression yang oke buatku, yaitu rasa masakannya yang enak banget. Berbagai macam masakan yang dibuat dari jamur. Untuk selain jamur, nampaknya ada, namun pilihan jamurnya enak. Tastenya enak. Pas aja.

Kalau di sana menu ya juga bervariasi, jadi tidak akan bosan. Kalau menurut lidahku, sate jamur paling enak, dari semua olahan jamur di sana.

Untuk ketersediaan meja makan juga banyak. Mushola, toilet, dan parkir juga aman. Nah pegawainya Jejamuran banyak, jadi tidak akan lama menunggu. Di sana juga ada toko oleh-oleh, khususya dari Jamur.

title: Jejamuran
name: kenanga tulodo
text:
tempatnya indah. banyak tanaman. kolam ikan .bagus untuk foto2
semua menu makananya seputaran jamur.. sate jamurnya kenyal enak
disini juga jual kaktus dan tanaman lainya
cocok buat yg vegetarian
lokasi tidak terlalu jauh dr jalan utama yogya - magelang

title: Jejamuran
name: Iwan Habib
text:
Suasananya cukup oke, fasilitas oke ada, taman bermain anak kecil, terapi ikan, Mushollah dan toilet umum.

Untuk masakan sangat enak, olahan jamur nya melebihi ekspektasi. Bahkan seperti tidak memakan jamur.

Untuk yang tidak menyukai jamur jangan khawatir, masih terdapat menu lain seperti ayam goreng, ikan patin dan lain sebagainya.

title: Jejamuran
name: Elisabet Ratna W
text: Sesuai nama restonya semua makanan disini berbahan dasar jamur, mulai dari sate, gulai, sop, etc. Cocok untuk kaum vegetarian. Meskipun begitu juga ada menu ayam gorengnya. Tempat luas, nyaman, bersih, dan asri sekali. Cocok untuk family dining atau kumpul dengan teman2. Resto RECOMENDED kalau main ke Jogja. Aksesnya juga mudah bagi disabilitas disediakan pula wheelchair.

title: Jejamuran
name: Tri Hantarawati
text: Berbagai macam olahan makanan serba jamur, paling suka sate jamur nya, setelah kuliner jogja yg serba daging maka saatnya pilih makanan serba jamur ini, parkir luas, anak sy paling suka dg terapi ikan, sambil main air

title: Jejamuran
name: Titus Agung Nugroho
text: Jejamuran resto terletak di jalan Pramuka, RT.01 / RW.20, Niron, Pandowoharjo, Kabupaten Sleman, Yogyakarta dan mulai buka sejak jam 9 pagi hingga 9 lewat 10 malam. Restoran ini membuat jamur menjadi beragam jenis makanan mulai dari sate, tongseng, jamur krispi dan bahkan ada es dawet jamur. Suasana disini sangat enak dan ada dua tempat makan, yang satu di dalam ruangan ac dan yang satu di luar ruangan (non ac). Dihalaman nya terdapat kolam renang ikan dan hawanya pun sejuk jadi sangat enak buat menikmati makanan yang ada. Ada juga photobooth gitu dengan latar belakang tanaman jamur gitu. Ada kolam terapi ikan dan toko oleh-olehnya. Tempat parkir mobil sangat luas di seberang jalan dan juga ada agak jauh tapi sekitar 300 meter dari lokasi restoran, tapi ada kendaraan yang ngantar kita ke restorannya kok. Cocok untuk santap siang saat pergi dari arah magelang dan mampir kesini. Untuk harga, cukup mahal karena ini restoran dan sudah terkena ppn. Makanannya enak dan pelayanannya juga oke.

title: Jejamuran
name: Teguh
text:
Hampir seminggu muter Yogyakarta kulineran cuma ini yang memuaskan. Recommended banget. Harga semurah cafe gerobak pinggir jalan tapi kecepatan pelayanan dan kenyamanan tempat seperti bintang 5. Sampai toilet pun lebih terurus dari umumnya restoran. Rasa masakan tak perlu diragukan. Headhunter boleh nih ngincer managernya 🤑
Plus: lokasi ramah disabilitas, disediakan kursi roda dan tangga alternatif.

title: Jejamuran
name: Dyah Dhani
text: Semua makanannya enak, disajikan secara cepat, gak pernah nunggu lama, semuanya terorganisir, ada spot jual tanaman juga, dan memberi makan ikan di kolam. Cocok untuk makan siang keluarga

title: Jejamuran
name: siti aminah_akun
text: Menjadi andalan kalau ada agenda makan-makan kantor dalam rangka perayaan atau apa pun itu. Bisa reservasi dulu kalau mau makan di sini dalam jumlah banyak orang. Pelayanan makanannya cepat dihidangkan hangat-hangat. Waktu ke sini pesan menu paket ternyata yang datang banyak sekali sampai kenyang semua. Yang paling favorit di sini sate jamur dan tongseng jamurnya, bisa bikin ngabisin nasi. Kalau menu paket minum teh-nya bisa minta dipisah dengan es, jadi nanti per orang sesuai selera mau minum teh pakai es atau tidak. Kalau ternyata pesennya kebanyakan tenang aja, bisa minta dibungkus kok buat yang belum termakan. Fasilitas di sini ada mushola, toiletnya juga banyak dan bersih, kalau pas pulang bisa mampir lihat aneka olahan jamur di pintu keluar siapa tau mau dijadikan oleh-oleh. Kalau pas menyeberang jalan mohon ikuti arahan Pak Satpam ya supaya aman bagi pengunjung maupun pengguna jalan lainnya. Kalau pas lagi di Sleman jangan lupa mampir ya Sobat!

title: Jejamuran
name: Cakra Satriyadana
text: Sudah kedua kalinya saya makan disini dan saya sangat puas dengan semua makanan yang disajikan, Favorit saya sendiri yaitu sate jamur dan Jamur Penyet. Untuk minuman saya rekomendasikan es dawetnya. Pelayanannya termasuk bagus dan cekatan. Rekomendasi bagi para wisatawan dari luar kota yang ingin mencoba makanan maupun minuman yang dibuat dengan jamur.Untuk foto makanannya saya lupa karena sangking enaknya hahahaha....

title: Jejamuran
name: mas Wok
text: Masakan serba olahan jamur soal rasa tdk mengecewakan, tempat strategis pinggir jln raya, tempat parkir untuk bus dan mobil sangat luas 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

title: Jejamuran
name: ropiatu jaliah (Opipolla)
text:
Superrr recommend

Rasa makanannya ga ada yg ngecewain.
Sate jamur rasanya kaya daging sapi
Sop jamur nya enak, kuahnya seger banget cocok buat anak2 juga
Tongseng jamur nya jga enak banget
Bothok nya enak. Semua enak

Pelayanan cepet ga pake nunggu lama padahal pelanggannya jg banyak

Harga termasuk murah, 8 orang habis sekitar 500rb

Tersedia jg snack corner utk oleh2 dan beberapa spot utk foto2

Kalau malam ada live music gamelan dan sinden nya

title: Jejamuran
name: ANDRIE MR
text: Makanannya serba jamur dan rasanya luar biasa enak. Harga juga tidak terlalu mahal. Ada terapi ikan dengan berendam kaki digigit ikan-ikan kecil. Toilet bersih. Ada musholah. Parkir gratis. Dibayar juga nolak ga mau terima, luar biasa.

title: Jejamuran
name: natri santoryuu
text: Pengalaman makan yang sangat berbeda dengan POV sebagai seorang vegetarian. Enak dan ndk nyangka jamur bisa dibuat makanan seperti itu

title: Jejamuran
name: safitri ayuu
text:
Tempatnya luas bangeetss, awal masuk di sebelah kanan ada tempat budidaya jamurnya. Awal masuk dikasi nomer mejanya, buku menu, kertas orderan.
Fasilitas nya lengkap, sampe ada ruang laktasinya.
Harga menunya murah2, rasanya juga mantap. Saya pesan sate jamur, tongseng jamur, geprek jamur. Semuanya enak apalagi sate sama gepreknya, gak berasa lagi makan jamur.
Dijalan keluar ada tempat terapi ikan gratis, spot2 foto, kolam ikan (ikannya banyak banget gaeess), juga ada oleh2 berbahan dasar jamur.
Area parkirnya ada di seberang, parkiran luas dan gratis. Ada kios yg jual oleh2 jg diarea parkir.
Pokoknya kalo ke jogja harus mampir di jejamuran 😍

title: Jejamuran
name: Violita Angelina
text:
Tempatnya luas, cocok untuk keluarga besar ataupun rombongan.
Parkiran luas, tersedia untuk parkir bus.
Menu sangat banyak dan variatif, tidak hanya jamur
Ayam goreng recommended
Harga tidak terlalu mahal
Ada kolam terapi ikan
Lokasinya mudah dijangkau

title: Jejamuran
name: Andyka S.
text:
Saat datang, ada resepsionis bagian depan untuk menanyakan jumlah pengunjung. Apabila meja tersedia langsung diarahkan ke meja berapa dan diberikan menu serta kertas pemesanan.

Makanan nya cukup terjangkau. Ada paket untuk sekeluarga juga.
Makanan yang paling recommend adalah sate jamur. Entah kenapa rasanya masih terbayang sampai sekarang.

Setelah makan, selagi menunggu makanan turun, bisa menyelupkan kaki ke dalam kolam terapi ikan. Rasakan sensasi sel kulit mati kita digigit oleh ikan ikan kecil secara gratis tanpa biaya 👌🏻

Setelah selesai bisa langsung ke kasir dan keluar sesuai arah petunjuk.
Arah keluar melewati tempat toko oleh-oleh yang berisi makanan jamur juga 👍🏻

title: Jejamuran
name: Reinta Wardhani
text:
Bukan kali pertama kesini. Untuk rasa makanannya masih sama dan masih konsisten serta cukup enak.

Mantap.

title: Jejamuran
name: Silfia Fariasih
text:
Terkahir kesini 5thn yg lalu super rame parkiran penuh.
Sekarang sudah ga se padet dulu ga perlu antri lama
Rasa masakan masih sama enak cuma prosinya berkurang.. Maklum inflasi

title: Jejamuran
name: why-studio
text: Varian menu jamur yg di masak rendang, goreng crispy, sop, dll... Cocok untuk menu makan siang bareng tim...

title: Jejamuran
name: sheilly yuliani
text:
tempatnya besar banget. makanannya enak-enak walaupun olahan dari jamur. sangat rekomendasi untuk bawa keluarga dan teman ke sini.
restoran yang menurut saya sederhana tapi servisnya luar biasa melebihi hotel berbintang. disediakan payung besar ketika hujan, dibantu menyebrang jalan, ada akses jalan untuk kursi roda, ada pangkalan ojek online, ada terapi ikan gratis, ada traditional live musiknya juga, dan ada 1 lemari yang isinya barang-barang pelanggan yang ketinggalan. VERY VERY GREAT SERVICE.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nanda Hidayat
text: Nyaman buat makan bareng keluarga, luas bersih, makanan ya standart (tidak mengecewakan)

title: Jejamuran
name: Icha
text: Always enjoy my lunch time here!! I tried a cold drink made from mushrooms (summer breeze) and I liked it even though it tasted strange at first ..... The food is always delicious and served quickly.

title: Jejamuran
name: Novieta Christina
text: sate jamur paling enak, bumbunya kyk sate ayam. suasananya juga enak, jadi pesan makanan banyak bisa pelan2 makan dan bs habis semua.

title: Jejamuran
name: Palastri Shop
text:
Suasana : ada penyanyi dan live musik.
Staff : sangat membantu, ramah.
Saya minta dinyanyikan lagu happy birthday 🎈🎂 untuk keluarga. Dan staff sangat membantu. Perayaan ulang tahun keluarga menjadi makin meriah

Tempat : luas dan lebih luas dari sebelumnya. Mampu menampung banyak tamu. Cocok untuk keluarga

Makanan : sempurna, enak semuanya

title: Jejamuran
name: Wisam Zuhdi Surya Nusantara
text: Rumah makan yang banyak menyediakan makanan dari olahan jamur mulai goreng, bakar, pedas, manis, asin, penyet. Ada juga sup, mie , tomyum, lumpia, nasi goreng dengan harga standar restoran tapi worth it. Restoran ini memiliki parkiran sangat luas untuk mobil, roda dua sampai bus. Lokasinya sangat terjangkau karena di pinggir jalan raya lintas kota-provinsi. Ada kolam ikan terapi. Ada tempat oleh oleh. Ada musholla dan toilet (sayang agak kotor). Untuk minuman juga lengkap mulai susu, teh, jeruk, kopi

title: Jejamuran
name: Ratnasari Dewipurnama
text: Tempatnya nyaman dan sangat luas sejuk serta makannya enak2 rasa makan an yg semuanya jamur namun rasnya tak seperti jamur favorit nya adalah sate jamur nya.

title: Jejamuran
name: Aulia Alyda
text:
Dari semua yg saya pesan yg outstanding hanya tahu bakso jamur 💯
Portabello telur asin nya enak, agak nyesel ga pilih varian potabello semua aja.
Minuman honey lime tea enak seger, ga terlalu manis.

title: Jejamuran
name: Andri Fahlevi
text: Tempat luar biasa untuk pecinta jamur! Semua menu di sini luar biasa enak. Pelayanan ramah dari tukang parkir hingga staf restoran. Parkir luas, membuat kunjungan semakin nyaman. Sungguh tempat yang luar biasa untuk menikmati berbagai hidangan jamur yang lezat.

title: Jejamuran
name: Maghfiroh Alfajriyah
text: Ada banyak menu jamur yang sangat beragam dan juga enak dengan harga yang terjangkau. Selain untuk dimakan, ada juga jamur yang dipajang untuk sekadar dilihat (bagi yang ingin melihat-lihat jamur) dan dibeli terutama jamur Lingzhi yang berguna sebagai obat. Sambil menunggu pesanan, pembeli juga bisa foot therapy dengan baby fish yang ada di sisi-sisi tempat makan. Pembeli bisa memilih tempat duduk dimana saja karena Jejamuran memiliki tempat yang sangat luas. Musholla yang disediakan juga bersih dan nyaman.

title: Jejamuran
name: Innas Hasna
text: Baru kali ini menemukan restoran yang bikin happy! Makanannya semua (yang dicoba) enaaaak! Pengunjung banyak banget, tapi ngga ada waiting list. Waiters selalu standby. Orderan datengnya cepet banget. Almost perfect! Hampir segala aspek sampai detail terkecil pun dipikirin. ❤❤❤❤❤

title: Jejamuran
name: Elton Wilmot
text: Stopped with friends for early lunch. Place was quite because it was still early and raining. Vegetarian dishes with a large variety and so many incredible flavours fused into mouth watering dishes. Food was vibrant, flavorful, full of colours and portions are good and priced well encouraging you to try different mixes and options. Staff were pleasant, service was quick. Beautiful gardens and water features to explore and there is a gift shop selling foods and clothing. Not being vegetarian I was pleasantly surprised by what can be done with the right ingredients and some creative flair.

title: Jejamuran
name: Dennis De Witt
text: Everything here is about mushrooms and all in the menu is made from mushrooms, even sate. It was all delicious. Our tourist guide Mr Yoga brought us here after visiting the Borobudur Temple and we enjoyed the food and nice atmosphere.

title: Jejamuran
name: Diviezetha A. Thamrin
text:
Very interesting and exciting concept with vast range of varieties of mushrooms! A very fun way to showcase mushrooms and elevate vegan cuisine as well.

Love the idea and the concept. A few menu might be stretching it a bit and might not have the best balance, but still truly appreciate their creative ideas.

title: Jejamuran
name: Cuanday Official (Ga Cuan, Ga Makan!)
text: A must-visit in Jogja! Loved their creative mushroom dishes — fresh, tasty, and full of unique flavors. The place is spacious and has a fun local vibe. Stayed a while after eating to check some Cuanday trading signals. Great spot to enjoy good food and sneak in a little market watch.

title: Jejamuran
name: Vannessa Adrienne
text:
A Must-Visit Culinary Spot in Yogyakarta! 😍🍄

If you’re planning a trip to Yogyakarta and looking for a unique culinary experience, Jejamuran is a place you shouldn’t miss. Eating at Jejamuran was undeniably one of the highlights of the Yogyakarta trip. The creativity in turning mushrooms into such diverse and flavorful dishes is impressive, even for non-vegetarians. It’s perfect for those who are looking to try something different yet authentically Indonesian.

🍄‍🟫Here are some recommended dishes you absolutely must try:

🍛 Tongseng Jamur
🥦 Tumis Brokoli Jamur
🫔 Botok Jamur : Wrapped in banana leaves and steamed, the botok jamur is fragrant, soft, and bursting with earthy umami flavors. It’s subtly spiced, with grated coconut enhancing the natural sweetness of the mushrooms.
🍢 Sate Jamur : One of Jejamuran’s most popular items. The mushroom satay is grilled to perfection, slightly crispy on the edges, and doused in a rich, nutty peanut sauce.

Overall 10/10

title: Jejamuran
name: Yoses Ernest Prawinulat
text:
Jejamuran Resto – A Must-Visit Mushroom Paradise in Yogyakarta!

If you're looking for a unique culinary experience in Yogyakarta, Jejamuran is the perfect spot. Specializing in mushroom-based dishes, this family-friendly restaurant offers a wide variety of creative, flavorful, and healthy menu options—from mushroom satay to crispy mushroom nuggets and even mushroom rendang!

The setting is spacious, clean, and beautifully designed with a natural, green atmosphere. It also features a mushroom cultivation tour area and photo spots, making it more than just a place to eat.

Prices are affordable, service is fast and friendly, and the food is consistently fresh. Whether you're a vegetarian or simply curious about mushroom cuisine, Jejamuran is worth the stop.

Highly recommended!

title: Jejamuran
name: 김상민
text:
족자카르타 여행중 운전 기사님이 추천해주셔서 우연히 온 레스토랑인데 입구랑 분위기부터 우선 너무 시원하고 깔끔한데다 천장도 높고 오픈되어 있어서 좋았습니다. 게다가 온통 버섯??넘 신기한 컨셉이라 재미도 있고 첨부터 들떴음🤭 구글 리뷰에 보니까 sate jamur(버섯꼬치), jamur rendang(버섯 른당) 뭐 이렇게 많이 시키길래 시키고 jamur bakar pedas, jamur tongseng, nasi goreng jamur, kangkung, toge 등등 여러가지 시켜서 먹었어요 근데 너무 놀란게 다 맛있음….💗 가장 추천 메뉴는 역시 모든 사람에게도 favorite인것 같은 사테 자무르, 른당 자무르 이렇게였고 전 개인적으로 많이 맵긴 하지만 bakar pedas도 밥이랑 숙주, 모닝글로리 이렇게 같이 먹었을 때 넘 입이 즐거웠습니다❤️❤️🤭 일단 버섯 좋아하시는 분들은 무조건 꼭 꼭 x 10000 와서 먹어야 하는 버섯계의 미슐랭이고, 진짜 이 버섯 레토랑을 알게 된 사실만으로 하루종일 기분이 좋을 정도로 추천드립니다(당연 비건/베지테리언도 추천) . 혹시 버섯을 안좋아하시는 분이라면 여기 생선, 닭고기구이 이런 메뉴도 있고 맛도 있기 때문에 걱정할 필요 없습니다😊
족자카르타 여행 마지막날에 알게 되어서 다시 한번 더 못 먹고 가는 게 아쉽네요..!
정말 맛있습니다. Jaejamuran the best restauran in Jogja!!!⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

title: Jejamuran
name: Poppy Fedora
text: New experience for non vegetarian for having foods. The meal was delicious and tasty

title: Jejamuran
name: felix liauw
text: The mushroom satay, rendang, and tongseng are good to try. But the salted egg mushroom tastes not so good. The mushroom (enoki) dawet ice is unique.

title: Jejamuran
name: Kimberly Khor
text: Brilliant place that celebrates mushrooms in the most delicious ways you could imagine. Personal favourite was the Javanese mushroom curry.

title: Jejamuran
name: R K
text:
Came here to have early lunch with friends and we did not know that we had chatted with  Bp. Ratidjo. He was very calm, friendly and I really pleased having conversations with him.
We ordered many kind of foods, purely from all kind of fungi/mushrooms. They were excellent and exceptionally good, I never really know they were so delicious. We enjoyed the mushrooms drinks too. I really recommend to bring your family and friends to enjoy alternative non-meat (and good) foods.
The atmosphere is an open concept, clean and simple. They have friendly staffs and patients especially when dealing with my kids (picky eater).

title: Jejamuran
name: syarafia abdsamad
text: Kebanyakan cendawan ada jugak ayam goreng ikan goreng kedai bersih tempat solat besar sesuai Untuk Keluarga & anak2 yg masih kecik

title: Jejamuran
name: Somkhit Wilailak
text: อาหารส่วนใหญ่ ทำมาจากเห็ด รสชาดอร่อยมาก สะอาด ราคาค่อนข้างถูก แนะนำครับ

title: Jejamuran
name: Ratri Andinisari
text: Love the food!! 95% of the food is tasty. Can’t believe that all of those were vegetarian. They also sell a lot of products made from mushroom. Will definitely go there again. A suitable place for family gatherings.

title: Jejamuran
name: Banuaji P
text: Nice taste of mushroom. They have many choice of food related of the mushroom. And they have many type of mushroom. The mushroom is good and not stinky. You can buy gift for your fams at home at their store at the exit area. You can also booked the ac area for your group. And you can enjoy free fish therapy for your feet.

title: Jejamuran
name: Rahardhyani Dwiannisa
text: Yummy food, good service, came during lunch time and directly got a seat. We loved the jamur rendang and creamy mushroom soup. Ayam bakar was also very soft and good!!

title: Jejamuran
name: Raymond Dharma
text:
A restaurant that serves primarily mushrooms based dishes. The restaurant itself is very spacious, a lot of parking area available, so don't worry about parking space. The atmosphere is javanese, with plenty of garden area.

The meal itself is very unique because they serves mushrooms in many ways. Taste excellent and you won't believe that mushrooms can be cooked in so many ways yet still be very delicious. Definitely a must try restaurant if you ever visiting Yogyakarta.

title: Jejamuran
name: TTHP
text: Unique concept. This place focus on mushroom, either for the food or other product as well. I try their tongseng and satay, both taste pretty good. Price is not too expensive. They have souvenir too

title: Jejamuran
name: Asri Aldila Putri
text:
The food was good. I personally love the eggs with mushroom, it's sooo soft (my fav). Others are good too.

The service are excellent. It was quick and fast respond when we asked for extra plate, sambal, etc. They also cleaned the table and floor right away once the guest next to us finished their lunch. I like clean restaurant.

Thanks!

title: Jejamuran
name: Gede Darma
text: The food here was super nice and affordable. They offered all kind of mushroom-dishes from satay to gulai. They also sell gifts, cacti & succulent, and snacks (the mushroom chips is good to buy). The space is very very spacious.

title: Jejamuran
name: Fairuz Anatasya
text:
As the name goes, all menus here have mushroom ingredients including the dawet (and it tastes a bit different but still tasty). The satay is also juicy but lack of seasoning. The location is a bit far from the city.

Overall is excellent.

title: Jejamuran
name: Carissa Geneviene
text:
Jejamuran is the best resto in Yogyakarta! Even for those who don’t like mushroom must give this place a second chance as their love to cook mushroom is to the moon 👍🏼 They really know how to cook and process mushroom into delicious dish. The variety is great and they always evolve. Always love coming here despite the distance. No one cook mushroom like this across Indonesia even.

Bottom line is, A MUST TRY!!! if you offered to come here and u reject for whatever reason (except allergy maybe), what’s wrong with you? 😂 Seriously try it!

Recommended: Sate Jamur, Jamur Penyet, Risoles Jamur. Their portion is a bit on a smaller side so you can definitely double the order per usual portion.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nida Irmanti
text: Probably most interesting restaurant in jogja. It started off as an effort to distribute harvests from local mushroom farmers and has since developed into a full blown attraction of its own. All their dish, even some beverages, are mushroom based. Everything was tasty and reasonably priced. The whole venue was airy and spacious, with live mushrooms at the entrance, and even free fish therapy for you to soak your feet in! Ya

title: Jejamuran
name: Farras Hanif
text: This is the place to go for mushroom dishes; it has a wide variety of menu items. They also offer snacks and ice cream. It has mini playground facilities and fish ponds for children to play.

title: Jejamuran
name: Yohanes I.
text:
Nice place that offer a nice mushroom based dish. They provide the dish nicely that you'll not recognize this is a mushroom dish and nor some "weird texture correct flavor" dish.
I recommend their fried portobello as the most liked menu (i repeatedly order)
Their satay also nice but don't expect 100% replication of chicken one

title: Jejamuran
name: soraya begum
text: One of the reasons customers will come back to the restaurant is because of their food.  Since the first time my hubby visited the restaurant in 2019, he kept insisting that I visit the resto. I think I understand why, and I can say that jejamuran can provide us with delicacy of traditional/indonesian cuisine. Almost all the menu I ordered here is taste superb (except for spicy/'edan' food selection. It's just too spicy for my liking, so I couldn't finish eating it). The restaurant is big, it has a souvenir shop with their specialty product (containing mushrooms). The restaurant is also selling orchid, cactus and succulent  plants, so you can bring the plants into your home. I can say that jejamuran is a great place for eating with your family/friends with a very nice scenery. However, I think in general, prices can be considered as expensive in the Jogja area. I spent around IDR 125k/person to eat here (including beverage). I also bought tea, canned food, chips, etc from the souvenirs shop around IDR 150k. The parking area is spacious, very nice, but so many illegal parking/people ask for money claiming they help us park our vehicle (even though the sign clearly says 'free parking fee').

title: Jejamuran
name: Fred Griffiths
text: Delicious mushroom based menu. Very unique and reasonably priced (160k for mushroom omelet, mushroom skewers (satay jamur), mushroom fried rice, and beef and mushrooms plus tea, coffee, and water). We also feds the koi which was fun!

title: Jejamuran
name: Frissie Dhitta
text:
I love ambience of the restaurant. As you step into the entrance, you'll find the beautiful mushroom plants with water vapor. And there is spot photo that you can use to take picture.

Main course in Jejamuran 90% made from any kind of mushrooms. The taste is great!
For beverage, you must try summer breeze with enoki topping. Perhaps it looks weird but surprisingly good 😻

title: Jejamuran
name: Ardian Nugroho
text:
If you are a mushroom lover or vegan, this place is perfect for you. They provide meals with mushrooms as the main ingredient, like mushroom satay, tengkleng mushroom, and many more.

The place is big and has a good space. They applied a good health protocol.

You can also buy canned mushrooms with various taste here. The service is good, though.

They also provide a big parking lot.

title: Jejamuran
name: Beta Antoni
text:
This place so comforting.
All food is very local and like moms cooking.

Recommend order Tongseng Mushroom, because its all good, gravy so strong, not to sweet and very balance.
Unfortunately Mushroom Satay is too cold. Maybe they grill first.

Mushroom enoki with salted egg is great combination, is very yummy.

And overall this restaurant having reasonable price (thats why i like) hahaha

title: Jejamuran
name: Dicky Bratawijaya
text:
Great food, great place

Once you come in inside the restaurant, you're greeted by selections of mushrooms, which you can purchase

Though the restaurant itself is not a vegetarian restaurant, you can enjoy varieties of mushroom's cuisine
And the price is quite affordable

After that, you can try submerging your feet into their fish pond and feel tens of fish eats you dead skin cells. It feels a bit ticklish

title: Jejamuran
name: Adzkia Ra'ida Salma
text: It's one of the busiest food destination in the city, that's why it's very large and usually you can only can get into the restaurant with waiting list. They have great system, great service, great facilities, and of course, great foods. I love how diverse the mushroom menus in here. Definitely such a fun experience.

title: Jejamuran
name: Hardiansyah Hardiansyah
text:
The place is huge, it serves all mushroom dishes. Personally, I love the soup. The soup is clear and taste so refreshing and light.
Im not a fan of the satay, but tastes not bad.
The fried mushroom is just ok.
There is a pond, where you can do relaxation by letting your feet to be tickled by the fishes. It is a weird sensation, at least try once. There is a souvenier place for you to buy mushroom and many other stuffs as well. There is some activities for knowing more about mushroom. Overall, it is a good experience.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nurul Aini Fadilah
text:
I love the food. It tastes good and tasty. The price is affordable also. All the food are from mushroom, they have so many variants such as mushroom rendang, satay, roasted mushrooms and so on. The tea is really good I love it.

The place is wide and cozy, but people smoke freely here so smoke are everywhere and quite smelly. Hope it will regulated better.

title: Jejamuran
name: Ch Nisaa, SSi
text:
The best place to enjoy your time with your Grub or a familly. 👨‍👨‍👧‍👧
There are many activities at the location example Painting, discussion Grub and etc..
This is third time, I was came to Jejamuran Restaurant 🥰, meanwhile the communication to serve place and chosen the menu is simple.

The best food recomendation 5⭐ value is Sate Jamur, Pepes Jamur, Tongseng Jamur, Lumpia Jamur, Jamur Bakar Pedar.

Now, The Jamuran place 🍄 are restaurant design not only mushroom but you can find with aglonema, fish pond, kids play ground and another speciment of mushroom photoboth in front of the place.

There are another photos from The Jejamuran 📸
Hope this review should be reference you to get this experience place in Sleman ✨✨

title: Jejamuran
name: Diana Lampung
text: The best restaurant in Yogyakarta! All of menu is delicious, we love it! We have enjoyed at fish therapy foot, we will come back again!👍🏻

title: Jejamuran
name: Tomi Taladin
text:
The storefront is very convenient and well-thought to avoid long queue of the car. It is as if they want your first impression to be perfect with easy drop-off and traditional storefront.
The food here is all made of mushroom. Sorry, let me correct that.. the food AND drinks here are all made of mushroom. And the taste is very delicious that I need to comeback here and try they wide selection of food.
They also sell canned dish of their several favourite dishes. I took home some I did not have chance to taste here.

title: Jejamuran
name: Syauqi Haris
text: Great place for group or family, healthy menu, fair price for taste. Mushroom satay is the best. Helpful staff too :) oh i forgot, many photo spots if you wanna get instagramable pictures here, awesome (y)

title: Jejamuran
name: Martina Daruli
text: Love this place. The mushrooms are everywhere!!! Although it was crowded, the service was still great. Parking lot quite big and shuttle car was provided from parking lot to the restaurant vice versa. Easy to get table, fast service, cheap but delicious foods and drinks. Also you can buy mushroom snacks for souvenirs here in good quality and prices. Love it!

title: Jejamuran
name: Keziah Tuerah
text: Almost all the dishes are made from Mushrooms! How interesting! They taste good too. Perfect to bring your vegetarian friends! The restaurant and parking space is enormous. They also have a store that sells mushroom snacks, and mushroom dishes stored in cans (like canned tunas, but its mushrooms).

title: Jejamuran
name: Ihda Maulida
text: Amazing restaurant. A very spacious and cozy restaurant. How they turn mushrooms into a very scrumptious dishes. Everything taste great with an affordable price. The place is always crowded, but they manage everything well, they make sure every guests will have seats. The staff also give an excellent customer service satisfaction. The parking lot is large. There are also clean restrooms available. One more good point about the restaurant is, they don't provide free wifi. Maybe, they suggest us to enjoy the food and the quality time we spend there.

title: Jejamuran
name: Flouren Vellamy
text:
First impression is fascinating. I'm a mushroom lover so I love the menus. Right of the bat, we can see the mushroom farm in the store. They have many varieties of mushrooms that I barely ever saw. They even have pink mushrooms, rather cute in my opinion.
.
The Grilled Shiitake is the best tasting dishes for me! Then the Salted Egg Fried Mushroom, next is Fuyung Hai Mushroom. Also, I can't believe even their Dawet has Enoki mushroom in it and still tasted good ❤️.
.
The place is very big, has many tables and chairs. Service is fast but they forgot 1 of my orders. All in all, it's a really good place to try something new and still tasted delicious. Very satisfied!

title: Jejamuran
name: Love,flower,world愛的花花世界
text: 特色菇菇料理。大部分的東西都不錯吃。價格實惠。

title: Jejamuran
name: Djoko Angklung Nugroho
text: Spacious room with mushroom based menu.  Savory and delicious like meat.  Very friendly and fast service.  Large parking area opposite the restaurant.  Prices are relatively affordable.  Can buy a variety of snacks from mushrooms.

title: Jejamuran
name: Jonas Becker
text:
Great place, great food, great value. We ordered waaay too much, the portions are not small. Our favourites were the katsu mushrooms and the grilled Portobello.

Just one suggestion: please use less plastic. The sauces on the side do not need to be in plastic containers. The cutlery doesn't need to be wrapped in plastic. Straws could also be from another material.

title: Jejamuran
name: Rakhmad Azhari
text:
Cozy place. Most of food are mushroom based (the name itself means mushroom, play on word). Great service, great vibe for having family together and having good time.

The owner is very kind and friendly. If you are interested in learning how to grow mushroom, he will teach you.

title: Jejamuran
name: Krishna Handoyo
text:
One of the best place for having meals with family. Large parking lot, large dine in area able to accommodate more than 100 person in 1 time. Healthy food is served here since it comes from kind of mushrooms. Separated area for smokers and non smokers. Also available free fish therapy while waiting our orders. Place is clean, quick response from waiters, all with very reasonable prices. In the way out, there is a souvenir shop to buy many kinds of mushrooms snacks.
Very recommended restaurant in Jogjakarta area.

title: Jejamuran
name: 大阪いのっち
text:
店内も綺麗で、味も美味しかったです。店員さんの接客も良かったのでいいお店でした。
駐車料金は無料
さらにお店の前の横断歩道には交通整理をしてくれる警備員さんが3名体制でお客さん、横断歩道を渡る人の安全を守ってくれていて安心しました。店は広く雰囲気も良かったです。少し残念な点は机の置いてる場所が一段高くその段差の近くの席に座り気付かずにトイレなどに行こうとしたら踏み外して転げかける事がありました。段差の所に段差があるとわかりやすいように何か目印があると嬉しいです。
店内にニレンフィッシュと言う魚がいます。説明すると長くなるのでかんたんに言うとドクターフィッシュみたいにな身体の角質を食べてくれるような魚です。すごく気持ちよくて良かったです( ´∀｀)

title: Jejamuran
name: Linda Tandayu
text: Loooooooove the place! A very authentic restaurant. A lot of varieties of mushrooms dish here, and they are all very delicious! and the price is cheap too! A very clean restaurant, nice food, fast service, cool and cozy ambience, very comfortable. Here you can feed the koi fish too (for 5000 rupiah you can get a small bowl for pellets), also there is a fish therapy for free!

title: Jejamuran
name: In My Cupz
text: My fave spot during Jogjakarta trip! Reminiscing past memories to dine with special person. Bring home goodies in a great price too.

title: Jejamuran
name: Mo's
text:
I'm glad that I had the chance to try this restaurant when I visited Yogyakarta for holiday, since heard so much hype about it.
All kind of mushroom menu and fresh. Mushroom satay is favorite here, a must try. Tongseng was way too sweet for my liking.
The restaurant it self is spacious, you can park your car easily. They have fish pond which you can give food (buy at cashier for 5k) which attract kids to play.

title: Jejamuran
name: Ayi
text: This is one of the best vegetarian places in Jogja, if not the best. It's kinda one stop place where you can have delish foods, learn about mushrooms, and buy their packaged products/souvenirs. The use a lot of kinds of mushrooms as the main ingredients. The foods are so delicious and my forever favourite is their sate jamur, well seasoned and the peanut sauce is to die for.

title: Jejamuran
name: Marcellino Adryan
text: Jejamuran offers a truly unique and delightful dining experience centered around the versatile mushroom. From satay to soups and snacks, the menu showcases the culinary creativity in transforming mushrooms into a diverse array of delicious dishes. Each bite is a surprising revelation, proving that mushrooms can be both versatile and flavorful. The additional option to purchase canned versions of their specialties and exclusive merchandise adds a charming touch to the overall visit. For mushroom enthusiasts or anyone open to culinary adventures, Jejamuran stands out as a must-visit, providing a tasty and memorable exploration of the mushroom kingdom

title: Jejamuran
name: Saga Sansan
text:
Food was great, tasty and unique, a bunch of menus with mushrooms as the main ingredient.
To ensure better experience and food texture, be sure to also order the fried mushrooms one if you are ordering many mushroom dishes (mushrooms are mostly soft).
The place is also great and cozy, although kinda wish there was better air cooler than just fans.
The place also provides mushroom and other unique tasting ice cream flavor.
Beside food, the place also offer gifts, raw vegetables, and mushroom plants(?) to purchase.
Definitely recommended to try the place out.
I would recommend trying the place if you are also going to Magelang or Kaliurang from Yogyakarta (and vice versa).

title: Jejamuran
name: Immanuel Aditya
text:
MUSHROOMS EVERYWHERE! As the restaurant name implies. The restaurant has become a well known place over the years, but it was my first time here and I was NOT disappointed.
Maybe I'm just such a mushroom lover, but I loved every dish I ate. The champions were the satay and rendang. The tom yum rounded my top 3 so far. They do have some non-mushroom option such as fried chicken and fried prawn if you do so prefer.
The service was nice and lightning fast. In 5 minutes from taking my order most of the dishes have already been served.
Most definitely will come back to try the other dishes and another round of that delicious mushroom satay.

title: Jejamuran
name: Akhmad Juanda
text: The food. Delicious food. I still don't believe that food with mushroom in it can be that good... Try their many options of food. I like their scramble egg with mushroom the best. Taste great when it's still warm. Sorry for the lack of the pictures of the food.. i underestimated the taste :p

title: Jejamuran
name: DurianBoy
text:
Great experience. A whole menu with mushrooms.  I've never seen something like that.
I suggest to visit this place for this magic experience.
The prices are very low and a lunch will cost u less than 200k IDR
The location is very particular, with a small garden, and a  vasc with fish feet therapy.

Super recomended

title: Jejamuran
name: FWPN
text:
The foods are so good!!! The first time I eat  a big meal without realizing that there's no meat.

Sate jamur is the mosy recommended!!! The jamur goreng & tongseng jamur are also good!

10 / 10 for food!

The place is also huge but there's no cool decors.

title: Jejamuran
name: syarif chandra
text: This restaurant should absolutely be in everyone's must-visit-place list during their visit to Jogjakarta. Based on its name, mushroom is the main thing here. It serves many kinds of food that includes mushroom as one of its ingredients. The taste is superbly delicious and the price is suoer cheap. The place is also very spacious and convenient for children. It also has a musholla and a very large parking lot.

title: Jejamuran
name: Gabriella Ardhya
text:
This restaurant serves various mushroom based menus that are vegan friendly. We tried mushroom satay, tongseng jamur, mushroom soup, and mushroom omellete, our favorite dish was mushroom satay with peanut sauce (tasted good, just like chicken meat). Their service was good, and this place has nice ambience.

Update: Went there again about a year after my last visit. Ordered mushroom satay (still my favorite), karedok (spicy), mushroom omellete (fluffy and melts-in-mouth kind of omellete), deep-fried mushroom, and fried mushroom with salted egg sauce (the sauce was not salty). Every dish is worth to try, and their price is still reasonable despite their consistent popularity. Their service was still top-notch, dish served warm in no time (not exaggerating). Definitely would come back again when I visit Jogja.

title: Jejamuran
name: Ruth Eveline
text: I like this restaurant so much!!! The place is large. The food were tasty. The family package was cheap, given the served menu.  The restaurant sells lots of canned mushroom menu. I bought the opor and rendang, and they tasted delicious. I would miss this place and would love to come back. Thanks Jejamuran 😍😍😍

title: Jejamuran
name: Heidiii
text: All food provided in this place is made from mushrooms. Various kinds of mushrooms are used in each menu, even when I order ice dawet, there are also mushrooms, enoki mushrooms. It is located about 30 minutes from Jogja city. The parking lot is spacious and there is no parking fee. There are Many security personnel and ready to help you when you will cross from the parking lot to Jejamuran. I visited this place during the holiday season so the conditions were very crowded. I had to wait around 30 minutes for my turn to get a table and start ordering food.  This restaurant is really spacious and the supporting facilities are also quite complete such as a small garden to take pictures with decorative mushroom backgrounds, lactation rooms, toilets, rest rooms, and prayer rooms.  The food served is very delicious. My favorite menu is mushroom satay. The price of each mushroom-based menu is also relatively cheap.  Besides that, there also sells some mushroom-based snacks. Very satisfied and highly recommend this place.

title: Jejamuran
name: Hitam Putih
text: One of the most unique restaurant in Yogyakarta, must try! Most of the dishes are made from mushrooms. They make "normal" dishes using that ingredient, such as sate, tongseng, soup, rendang, etc. It tastes like meat! And the most excellent thing in the restaurant is the service. They arrange the particular detail to make the guests feel comfortable. Such as the flow of the guests, quick service, free (and wide) parking, nice staffs, etc. They also have mushroom tour as well as souvenir shop! Recommended!

title: Jejamuran
name: A Markus
text: A restaurant where they make most of the food from the mushrooms. Satay Mushroom, Karedok Mushroom, Pepes Mushroom. But they still have some meat like bbq chicken or fried shrimp. Really tasty and healthy 👍👍👍

title: Jejamuran
name: revta fariszy
text: I brought my my family last time. it was a great choice i made. everything i ordered were super delicious and surprisingly cheap. there is like a mushroom plants on the front, great for taking photos.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nikolai
text: Went here with my wife, cool place with many variations of foods made from mushrooms ,service excellent and so fast , I'm surprised how this place so huge, perfect work! Have souvenir shop right there and tour to mushroom farm. We bought many dried and so delicious mushrooms. Really worth to visit if you have time in yogyakarta. It's a bit far away from the center ,prepare at least 2 hours for visiting this place. Prices in cafe is not so expensive and range between 10-50rb for dish.

title: Jejamuran
name: MARCIN KRÓL
text:
Pychota restauracja z daniami głównie z grzybów - samych ale tez z mięsem lub grzybami.
Ceny bardzo przystępne, obsługa super i szybciutko, choć trochę problem z angielskim :) ale zamawianie po zdjęciach działa OK
UWAGA - dodatkowa atrakcja gratis => Ikan fish teraphy - możesz zanużyć nogi w basenie z rybkami, które oczyszcza ci stopy z martwego naskórka 😁👍😂

title: Jejamuran
name: Alfi Pangestiawan
text: Unique experience here. I wasn’t expect to taste pretty delicious food here, turned out I was so wrong. The food we ordered were good: rendang, sate, tongseng, fried rice. My only problem was, I ate too much that time. But overall it was great to visit this place, taste the foods, and experiencing nice service from the staffs too.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nina Amelia
text: A nice place that serves various mushroom dishes. The place looks elegant and classy but the price is not exorbitant. The food is delicious. They have spacious dining area as well as parking area. Wheelchair access is available. Serving time is fast although restaurant is busy. Surely we will be back again if we visit Jogjakarta.

title: Jejamuran
name: Maria Putri
text:
great place for mushrooms lovers! all the foods here are delicious and quite cheap. It's a good place for family gathering or meeting-up with old friends.

Latest menu of October 4, 2024

title: Jejamuran
name: Handy Ban
text: The parking is spacious and free, there many varieties of dishes made with mushrooms and amazingly the taste is really great.

title: Jejamuran
name: Muhammad Fahri Priambudi
text: Mushrooms served in various menus, from stew, sauteed, soup, rendang, and satay. Cozy and casual place, and your child will loved it for sure. Interesting insights of mushroom cultivation and lot point of interests for taking pictures. You may try fish therapy here. Complete facilities and easy wheelchair accessibility available here. Visiting souvenir shop selling mushroom chips and canned mushroom is a must before you leave this wonderful restaurant. Surely will return here! Keep on the good work, Jejamuran!

title: Jejamuran
name: Titot Prayoga
text:
Oeannak sekali. My mum and dad suggested we try this place after we visited Borobudur. My eldest daughter didn't particularly like the various mushroom dishes, but luckily they had ayam bakar which she absolutely enjoyed. You wouldn't guess you'd be eating mushrooms. The textures, the flavour balance. My wife absolutely enjoyed the Tongseng Jamur - basically for her, it's a Thai red curry. Sate Jamurnya was something else! Meaty, full of umami. Love it.

For everything else, it was fantastic! Service, flavour, value. Sayang sih harus mabur dari UK untuk ngalami, dan gak tersedia magic mushrooms - Pasti ngetop ahah!

I suggested that Sonny Sides check this place out next time he's doing a culinary tour (plus, offer him shrums)

title: Jejamuran
name: Rimboen Mbun
text: Family restaurant with the cuisine of the various types of mushrooms, with supported of places to eat and the parking lot is spacious enough. Cuisine such as satay, beef rendang, tongseng in which it is a fungus that is no different with meat in general because the seasoning is so pronounced. That make cuisine here is so unique and delicious.

title: Jejamuran
name: Lutfi P
text: mushroom lovers? you will definitely like this place. you can find alot of food made of mushroom and it's delicious such as tongseng, sate, pepes, and even drink that have enoki mushroom as topping. The place is spaceful and enjoyable. Worth to try :))

title: Jejamuran
name: Putri Nuraeni
text: One of unique restaurant in Yogyakarta. They serve many dishes from mushroom or fungus, like tongseng, sate, rendang, soup and other. Beside of dishes they serve too many kind of snack and canned food for you to bring at home or souvenir for your friends and family. The place is quite big for more than 200 person. You can enjoy here with your friends and family.

title: Jejamuran
name: George
text: We stopped here on the way back from the Borobudar temple to Jogja center. We saw it on Google maps, highly rated as a mushroom restaurant and thought it sounded quite interesting. When we turned up it wasn't quite what we expected. There were security and parking attendants ready to guide us into a car park, from the middle of the road. There were also big busses in the car park. I didn't realise the place was so popular and big, I thought it was just a small restaurant. We went inside, and it was lovely. Live music was being played and it seems to be a hit with the Indonesian tourists, didn't see any other tourists like myself. It was very cheap considering how nice the restaurant was and importantly it was delicious. I really like mushrooms. Only complaint was that the Lumpia and Goreng Tepung Shiitake had obviously been cooked earlier as it didn't have the fresh crispness you would expect. But the Rendang Jamur, Tongseng Jamur and Sambal were excellent. Nice experience.

title: Jejamuran
name: Renata Krisnanti
text:
If I come back to Yogya, I definitely will eat here again!

The food was super great, worthy of the taste and price!

Tongseng jamur, the best tongseng ive ever eaten in my life.💙 This place is even greater for people who dislike eating meat or something needed to be bite for a long time.

This is a MUST VISITED PLACE if you come from outside Yogya, you cant find this kind of restaurant in any place in the world.

Highly recommend, especially for the tongseng 💙💙💙

title: Jejamuran
name: Fen
text: 有各式各樣的菇類料理，menu有附英文解說，環境舒適，分吸煙區及非吸煙區，還有販賣伴手禮和菇類特色商品!料理推薦sate !

title: Jejamuran
name: C H
text:
This is my favorite restaurant that I have EVER been to. A vegan paradise !! So many reasons to love it! Not only do they have delicious food and drinks, the warm atmosphere is also nice, they have a great mushroom store in the front and a wonderful snack shop with tons of mushroom snacks, AND they offer free ikan therapy while you wait for your food to arrive!! You must visit if you are going to any of the temples nearby (Prambanan and Borobudur being the most popular).

Great place for kids ☻ ☼

Try the nasi goreng with oyster mushrooms, and the friend oyster mushrooms. Also the drink made with wood apple syrup is AMAZING and an Indonesian favorite ☻ try it !

title: Jejamuran
name: Resa Anasto
text: The concept is unique. The food is great. The servants are very helpful. The parking field is vast and many parking officers were helpful. The ponds around was unique. Very recommended for you.

title: Jejamuran
name: Silvi Listijo
text: Good for vegan or not vegan. The taste is very unique. Fast serve also. Big place and can be reserved prior arrival. Thumbs up. Keep up the good work

title: Jejamuran
name: Stevanus Samuel
text: Very good taste, affordable price, the Mushroom Satay is taste Very Good and the fried rice Very Good too. the space is very spacious so you can bring friends and family here for party or gathering. Parking lot is in front of this place. They have mushroom cultivation, processed mushroom food (Canned and Chips). There is Javanese Live Music (Gamelan with Sinden) to entertaint you.

title: Jejamuran
name: Neni Wardana
text: This resto has many variations of mushrooms. I like it as mushroom is one of my fave food. For me,the Tongseng Jamur is the best! The resto is nice. Its toilet is clean. There is parking area rather far from resto but they provide shuttle for the visitor from parking area-resto-parking area. Staff is helpfull.

title: Jejamuran
name: 임에이미
text: 2 words : Vegetarian Heaven. A beautiful place, spacious parking lot too. Various choices of mushrooms cooked in every kind of way, don't misunderstand tho there's chicken and everything too. The food are really delicious and came shortly after we ordered. Its not only a restaurant includes a tour on mushroom plantation and other attraction. I guarantee a pleasant visit.

title: Jejamuran
name: Adji M. Akmal
text: I honestly didn't expect too much before coming to this place. But man, was I wrong. They have so many varieties of mushroom types and dishes, you just want to taste them all. One thing in particular was grilled shiitake. Tasty! 😁

title: Jejamuran
name: Danny Wongso
text:
Was awesome food

All menu was mushroom

You can enjoy rendang, satay, whatever was contain mushroom

Include the drink

Not so cheap but still at acceptable price

Very quick service

And you can enjoy fish foot spa

title: Jejamuran
name: Chin Li Li
text: 很特别的菌菇类的餐点，食物都有惊艳到我们，必须一试。餐后来一个蘑菇冰淇淋，赞！

title: Jejamuran
name: henry widodo
text: If you love musrooms, this is the place. Good food, excellent service and affordable price.

title: Jejamuran
name: Clayton
text:
This is an outside restaurant so the comfort will be whatever its like outside 😀
Having said that the portions are great and the food is great, fast service!
Make sure to ask for a tour of the mushroom farm if that is something you are into...

title: Jejamuran
name: Henricus Prabowo
text:
As simple as perfectly executed.
The food is great.
The atmosphere is decent.
There is a mushroom display to help you spent some time while waiting for the table.

title: Jejamuran
name: Gatot Adhi Wibowo
text:
Top Markotop!!! Must try yaaa. This resto has much foods and beverages and very delicious.
I eat Sate from Jamur. The taste is likely chicken sate.
I also eat tongseng...nice seasonings. I like it.
I order tom yum...nice taste and little bit 🌶
I also eat plecah kangkung....freshy brooo
Oya...Jejamuran already setting some decoration to take a picture. Not so many but good enough lah. Two years ago, there are so many spot to take picture, but i think they renoved the place so they can accommodate much more visitor to eat their food.
Ok...have a nice try yaaa

title: Jejamuran
name: Best of Denver
text:
“Jejamuran” serves everything mushroom! Aside from fast attentive service, delicious & cheap food, this restaurant also offers a free mushroom plantation tour, fish foot spa and live music. You’ll find this restaurant on the way back to Jogjakarta from Merapi Volcano or Borobudur Temple.
.
Upon entering the host gives you a menu and a table number.  Once you find your way to your table you mark your selections on the dim sum style menu.  If you come in the afternoon some of the popular items are usually crossed out as they sell out.
Be sure to brush up on your Indonesian as there is no English on the menu- or just resolve to be adventurous.

We tried the rendang mushroom, mushroom fried rice, mushroom satay, tomyum mushroom, kampung fried chicken along with avocado and unsweetened ice tea.

The food is ridiculously delicious - 5/5, drink/juice are ok. Too bad, the outdoor seating setting in this part of the world means the 2nd hand smoke is included free too 😤😤

We shall be back!

title: Jejamuran
name: Agustiawan Kurniadi
text:
A very Unique Resto. When you are nearby, you should stop and give it a try. Prepare to wait for your meal, but they are tasteful. Big place yet has enough parking spot, and manage professionally.
And ohh.. there is "fish therapy" for your feet

title: Jejamuran
name: Jason Budiarto
text: A very unique restaurant. They serve everything with mushroom, such Mushroom Rendang. We ordered mushroom soup, whole chicken, fried mushroom, mushroom tongseng and fried beancurd. My favourite is mushroom with spicy sambal. It is like penyet, but served with mushroom. At last, their price is unbelievable cheap. The whole thing only costs us 300,000 IDR.

title: Jejamuran
name: TENDY DEVELOPER
text: Good place and great food here. All menu are made from mushroom. So many mushroom variety cooked profeional here. You also could buy snack and parcel based mushroom here. Big lot parking available for car and buss. So why not come in

title: Jejamuran
name: Yu Hock Sim
text: Nice restaurant, almost all the dishes are made by mushroom. They provide set dinner for 5 or 3. So, dont have to worry if you dont understand the menu.. All are nice and tasty. Beside, there is a ole ole shop beside which you can bering some mushroom product to bring back with you.

title: Jejamuran
name: Lia Natalee
text: I always go to this resto everytime i visit Jogjakarta. The menu mostly is all about mushroom. My fave beverage is Summer Breeze which made of enoki mushroom n orange syrup. Its sour but taste good.

title: Jejamuran
name: Warta Erbetta
text: First time in Jogja to find the taste of Tom Yum soup as good and fresh as in Thailand. The place is nice, the foods are tasty and the price is reasonable

title: Jejamuran
name: Kenny Vincent
text: A must-visit destination. A place with collectives of mushroom based vegan meals. It is so so good. And for the quality and taste that we're getting, it is very cheap. If u visit. U have to try the "TONGSENG"

title: Jejamuran
name: Adri Prasetya
text: Lekkeeerrr pisan makanan beratnya...serba jamur ada masak sate pepes bakar tongseng tumis karedok botok tomyam sop....duhh sedeppp pisan

title: Jejamuran
name: aidan
text:
Pros: unique concept, great taste, quality services, clean, ample parking lot, nice facilities, fair pricing, air conditioned room available
Cons: understanably waiting time on busy hours on holiday seasons, so try to come early or later on lunch/dinner time

title: Jejamuran
name: Claudia P
text:
Very recommended! You can find dishes, chips, canned food and gelato made from the mushroom as their main ingredients.

You can find many types of mushroom, such as oyster mushroom, paddy straw mushroom, ear wood mushroom, portabello mushroom, button mushroom and etc.

I recommend you to try these dishes: skewed mushroom served with peanut sauce, rendang mushroom, salted egg mushroom, deep fried oyster mushroom and mushroom rissole.

The owner of the Jejamuran resto, Mr. Ratidjo very humble, he came to our table and ask how’s the taste and also say thank you to us.

title: Jejamuran
name: Fakhri Khaulany
text: You can eat all kinds of foods made from mushrooms. A suitable place for a culinary destination with your family. But this place is too crowded at certain times. And there are booth where various types of mushrooms are shown.

title: Jejamuran
name: Alifia N R
text: went to this place yesterday and it was soooooo good!! Their parking area is huge and it cost $ 0, it's free, wow! After entering the restaurant the front office asked me to consider if I still want to eat there or not bc few menus were sold out. Yes indeed a lot of dishes on the menu weren't available which is sad bc I really wanted to try Sate Jamur & Rendang Jamur, my friend told me that they tasted amazing. So, I tried Fuyunghai & Semur Pedas & Lumpia. And they're soooo goood. Affordable price! And they have Saparella! Also few traditional drinks like tape, soda gembira, etc. I went there in the afternoon and it was pretty hot bc it was smoking area (open). Maybe I'd choose their non smoking area if I go back later, bc they have AC in the room. Bc I couldn't order Rendang, I bought the can Rendang and it was soooo delicious! They gave us free tester! For the dishes n bakpia. As a Vegetarian, I did feel like finding a paradise hahahaa. Thank you xoxo.

title: Jejamuran
name: Rezk
text: Best vegan and vegetarian restaurants. There's a lot variant of mushrooms you can get here. Satai mushrooms, meetball without meet but mushroom, tempura mushroom and many other things. Very recommended even tough i dont really like the taste but it's really Worth it for you to try it. Very recommended place for family here. One of the best thing in thia place is the smoking place very little, evevn though I'm a smoker i really appreciate it

title: Jejamuran
name: Harley Anggakesuma
text: This place is awesome. You can order many types of food based on mushrooms ingredients. Limited parking lots near the restaurant, but they have another parking lot 200m after, and they provide shuttle bus from that parking lots for free. Parking is free anyway. Price is very cheap with nice taste of the food. Last orders at 9.30 PM... My suggestion this place is better place for dinner time. Cheers

title: Jejamuran
name: Tantri Budia
text: Beeessssttt resto so far.......I love any kind of mushroom. Their Mushroom satay is daa besttt.....you can find any other Indonesian style food with many kind of mushroom here. Worth to visit. You can also buy canned mushroom ready to eat.

title: Jejamuran
name: wahyu basjir
text:
I have been a fan of this restaurant since its early days. After nearly two decades, I still am and always love to dine in at Jejamuran. I witness its growth, and eventually realize that Jejamuran has no competitor that serves similar dishes.

Spacious halls with free flowing air under the roof are always ready for guests. The dishes are delicious at reasonable price and served in no time. Wheelchair access available from the front gate to your dining table.

title: Jejamuran
name: sina s
text: A very nice place to unwind, especially after you explore Magelang going back to Yogyakarta. Enough portion for an affordable price. Definitely a must visit.

title: Jejamuran
name: Mochammad Fathir Ma'ruf
text: very good restaurant... special food processed from mushrooms... all food from mushrooms... large parking area with ATM Centre, large restaurant, clean, large and modern pantry... also has gift shop... and small good mosque...

title: Jejamuran
name: Ika Rakhmawati Hilal
text: The best and the first Mushroom restaurant in Yogyakarta. You can find any mushroom cuisine here with international taste and traditional Javanese taste.

title: Jejamuran
name: Luca Balbi
text:
Amazing restaurant all dishes are made with mushrooms, it's really clean and cheap.
If you want you can put your foot on water they have small fishes for your skin.

title: Jejamuran
name: Asti Pinarti
text: My second visit, not as busy as the first. The food is delicious and healthy. All mushrooms. Love it !!!

title: Jejamuran
name: Jobs 78
text: Love this place, all different kind of mushroom and they cook in different way...so yummy specially fried mushrooms with chilly...and one more thing they have a fish therapy and it's FREE ... that fish tickle me to death 🤣🤣🤣 so fun though...

title: Jejamuran
name: Tia Tia
text: This place offers dishes that suit people's palates, even for vegetarians. The dishes are delicious and well made from mushrooms! Yes, mushrooms! The ambience is great as you can enjoy your meal accompanied by gamelan and Javanese songs played live. Also, there are photo spots for selfies, souvenir shops (selling mostly mushroom based food), and fish theraphy that you can enjoy while waiting for your ordered food. Anyways, if you go here during holidays and weekends, the parking space is soooo crowded that you have to park a bit far from the location. However, it is all worth it and,  there is so mushroom in my stomach that fits fungi like the ones served there.

title: Jejamuran
name: Anindita Kartika Wiraputri
text: I was there with my mother and her friends, we were like 70 people, we had booked in advance and when we got there, the foods were being served super fast. We went inside, sat, the foods were coming in about 5-10 minutes. It was really satisfactory esp for groups who had a packed schedule. The foods were delicious. My fav one is the mushroom satay (it tasted like a chicken satay, trust me). They also served several non mushroom menus so don't worry if you want to go with your friends but one of your friend doesn't eat mushroom, pick another dish instead.

title: Jejamuran
name: Tri Sarjono
text:
Visited on 2nd September 2022 for dinner.
Order many mushroom based menu : tongseng, soup, grilled shitake, fried portobello, telur dadar jamur, sate jamur.
Love the tongseng, sate jamur and fried portobello.
The place has spacious parking lot, the food served in quite short time, waiters were friendly too. Price-wise is not very expensive considering the taste (might be too much MSG, very thirsty in the morning on the next day), the portion, the parking space and also the friendliness.

title: Jejamuran
name: Rita Mutiara
text: mushrooms are processed with a variety of spices with a delicious taste, such as satay, black pepper, krispi, green lombok, guaranteed mushroom taste will not taste, like mushroom satay, which tasted like chicken satay, and the price of food is not too expensive

title: Jejamuran
name: Trio Budi A Susanto
text:
Good place to escape to enjoy jamur?
Yes, this place was jamur all around.
Affordable price

title: Jejamuran
name: Arya
text: The must-visit place to eat in Jogja, eventhough a bit far from the city center. They provide all kinds of dish made out of mushroom. They also have their own mushroom plantation nearby. The restaurant maybe packed during the weekends and nights, some of the menus are out of stock when we got here but the dishes we got is really delicious. My favourite was the sate and the gule, tender mushroom with good spices. Would really recommend all of the people to have a visit to Jejamuran while having holiday in Jogja.

title: Jejamuran
name: ZapoeR Oceh
text: For mushrooms lovers, this is your heaven. Cook different Indonesia dishes with the protein is replaced by mushrooms.

title: Jejamuran
name: Joe Felus
text: I enjoy the food especially grilled mushroom steak and the sate.

title: Jejamuran
name: Sylvani Thelma
text: Foods are so damn good. Price is still acceptable, but not that cheap ( i spent 130k for 2 persons) . All is mushrooms, make me eat a lot without feeling guilty hehe. Too bad that the receptionist(or waiter??) In front of the restaurant said it will take 40mins-60mins to get the seat because it was long holiday. Then i sit 5 mins, the waiter from inside call me to sit. I think they just want to rush us to get out? Or just lazy to check the queue? Better recheck again if they said so, it might 99% lie.

title: Jejamuran
name: Nagao (胖編)
text:
來到日惹不能錯過的蘑菇🍄主題餐廳，這是當地人聚餐最佳選擇，有蘑菇沙爹、糖醋蘑菇、蘑菇清湯、炸鮮鍋、蘑菇蛋捲等特色菜色，一定要過來吃！服務人員非常親切！也別忘了試試蘑菇茶唷！

即便離市區有近10公里的距離，來絕對不會後悔！

title: Jejamuran
name: Stefenson Alfa Tetelepta
text: Splendid, with multiple mushrooms-based foods.. very creative to produce mushrooms-based foods.. place is huge, parking area huge but separated with shuttle provided.. waiting time wasn't so long even in the peak hour..

title: Jejamuran
name: davidongky
text: Super big place and also fast serving. The taste is also superb. My favourite is tongseng and satay and also jamur bakar pedas

title: Jejamuran
name: Setyawan Antono, MBA
text: Mushrooms mushrooms 🍄 everywhere and delicious. The only place in Yogyakarta where you can eat all kind of mushrooms cuisines and learn about mushrooms. They have shop where you can get mushrooms snacks and souvenirs. It’s all worth coming here with your family as the have live music

title: Jejamuran
name: Nastiti Widya Ikhsani
text: Time to get MUSH(room)y 😆😆😆 these were the menus i ordered with my friends :3 forgive the angle but heyyy they taste good! We just love the ambience (calming live music), and how quick and efficient the service was. Lets not forget that they also provide fish spa and cool picture spots. This place is Wonka's Chocolate Factory for me, and I can be Charlie Bucket for mushroom foods :)

title: Jejamuran
name: Kumtornpol Buapatch
text:
ที่จอดรถ กว้างขวาง
อยู่ฝั่งตรงข้ามร้าน

เมนูเห็น และมีเนื้อสัตว์ เช่น ไก่ กุ้ง

title: Jejamuran
name: Eva Hänel
text: Fantastisches Restaurant! Als Vegetarierin ist es nicht immer leicht, in Indonesien abwechslungsreich zu essen, aber hier gibt es unheimlich viel in den unterschiedlichsten Variationen. Das meiste ist mit Pilzen. Der Service ist super. Einzig die Atmosphäre ist sehr wuselig und laut, das hat mich selbst jedoch nicht gestört. Klare Empfehlung!

title: Jejamuran
name: Susanto S
text: A must visited restaurant for people who love mushroom so much , from rendang, satay, soup, gulai ,all is amazing the taste . Originally and authentic.

title: Jejamuran
name: Julio Bagaskara
text:
Jejamuran, from its name, there is 'jamur' or mushrooms. Yes, this restaurant is a must go for mushroom lovers and culinary explorers in Jogja. This restaurant serves anything with mushroom! With different varieties and styles, from rendang, satay, tongseng, you name it!

The food are cooked so well and tasty! If you are confuse to choose the alá carte menu, there are food packets for 4-5 person. Aside of restaurant, Jejamuran also provides a shop selling yet another mushroom products, such as chips, canned mushrooms with different cooking styles (just like what they serve in the restaurant), and others.

Outside the restaurant you will see an edu park, showing every variety of edible mushrooms, this space is useful for learning, and also an instagramable spot to take your selfies! Parking spots are wide and abundant. Don't worry when you parked a little bit far from the restaurant, there are shuttles ready to take you to the doorstep of the restaurant reception table.

title: Jejamuran
name: Arif Fadilah
text:
A great resto that serve any kind of fungus. The service is really fast, and the price is reasonable.
I recommend you to bring your family or kids here.

title: Jejamuran
name: B. S.N.
text:
Crowd place, but always safety. With lot of space for parking cars and bus. Many food serve here in fast delivery, no long time for waiting our order.
Great management!

title: Jejamuran
name: Rosa Safa
text: Makanan dari cendawan. Murah dan sedap. Wajib makan disini kalau datang di jogyakarta. Very spacious restaurant. Good service. Ada tempat solat.

title: Jejamuran
name: Budi Sukma
text:
Poko'é kudu mampir mréné lurr, nek lewat opo neng sekitaran Sleman.
Tak Jamin Top Bgt lah....💖👌👍👍

title: Jejamuran
name: V. Listanto
text: Jejamuran means various of mushrooms. You can find most of Indonesian cuisine like sate, tongseng, rendang, sup, and asam manis in this restaurant. What makes it special? All of the dishes are made with mushrooms instead of beef or meat. Both of the taste and the serving are awesome The place is cozy and clean. You get free fish therapy as well in the fish pool near the eating area.

title: Jejamuran
name: Dhean Purnama
text: A nice place to visit if you are visiting Jogjakarta. They offer a variety of mushroom dishes that you can try. I personally love the "Mushroom Satay" and I highly recommend it. The sauce that they serve it with contain nuts, so if you are allergic ask for an alternative. The place also comes with a "Fish therapy" spot for free where you can dip both of your feet in the water have the fishes nibbles on your feet. If you are ticklish, I don't recommend it but otherwise just knock yourself out and relax. There's also a pond containing huge Koi fishes that you can admire. Last but not least, there is a small section near the enterence of the restaurant containing a display of different Mushrooms with labels on them. So if you're itching to "learn" something new before having lunch, this is your place.

title: Jejamuran
name: jean-pierre Debondy
text: Très bon restaurant où plein de plats sont préparés à base de champignons.  En plus en attendant ses plats ont peut se faire nettoyer ses pieds par des petits poissons😊😊😊

title: Jejamuran
name: rizza Maulana
text:
This was not my first time going here, but the food never stop to amaze me! Its not only great food, the price is also cheaper compared to other similar great restaurant.
Worth to come back when you go to jogja!

title: Jejamuran
name: Derin Rastiti Seftianingsih
text:
Their menu are so tasty 🥹🥹
I love the vibes and foods

title: Jejamuran
name: Marry Kusuma
text:
Most of the menu are made from mushrooms example: Satay is made from mushroom but served just looks like Chicken Satay.
Has spacious eating area and they managed the guest very well.
The order also quickly cooked and the price are affordable but the portion is a bit small.
Try Tongseng and Satay and you'll love it.
They also sell mushroom chips and canned mushroom outside the eating area.
Avoid lunch and dinner time as this place is popular among tourist and for those not having a car, can come here using taxi or online taxi such as Grab or GoCar.

title: Jejamuran
name: Lita K
text: Enjoy the meal, come from mushroom. You wont taste it like mushroom but gonna be looklike chicken n other thing. Delicious taste, cheap n get the experience.

title: Jejamuran
name: luluk harini
text: this restaurant serves various menu made from mushroom (in javanese, it's called jamur). Mushroom satay is my favourite. The place is spacious, including the parking lot. There is a nice photo spot as well

title: Jejamuran
name: Lee Tiam Kean
text: The owner of this restaurant has a great passion with mushrooms and obviously a champion in vegetarian. Although the menu consists of dishes like curry mutton, beef satay, sweet and sour fried chicken, fish ball soup etc, you will be surprised that all the dishes are made of different types of mushroom with different textures. They have a big kitchen for food preparation, drink preparation and dish washing area which are all separated. A must try...

title: Jejamuran
name: Ihsan Sutjipto
text: As the name suggests ("Jejamuran" is "Mushrooms" in Bahasa), you'd find a plethora of mushroom-based dishes here (Shiitake, Portabello, Merang, etc). Cozy and spacious place, though can be overcrowded on weekends or holiday season. Selection of foods are various and if you don't fancy mushrooms, there are other dishes too. Food tastes great and affordable (all the foods I posted on my picture costed me just about 125k IDR or about 10 USD). The drinks are just so-so though.

title: Jejamuran
name: Alvina Gunawan
text: Speciality in mushroom based meals since they have their own farm. Fast service, meals served in less than 15 minutes. Great for vege

title: Jejamuran
name: sunny soon
text: Reasonably, in fact cheap price, despite the renovated venue. With the consistent delicious selection of mushroom dishes. And i heard they also supported local farmers to participate in fair trade mushroom cultivation. Always looking forward to visit Jejamuran when I'm in Jogja.

title: Jejamuran
name: Eko Warisdiono
text: Menu tradisional versi jamur, tongseng, sate, karedok, sup

title: Jejamuran

text:
Wow its very good food for vege people indeed-two thumbs up,
Its very nice place to taste thier special Lunch. . . . .

title: Jejamuran

text: Extraordinary restaurant with great concept. You can eat mushroom base food, and they have outdoor place like ponds, and visitor can have fish terapy for free too

title: Jejamuran
